                            <comment id="14618479" author="leder" created="Mon, 16 Oct 2023 12:40:11 -0700"  >Interesting find, thanks a lot for checking! That Javadoc is partially generated from templates, which seem to produce ill-formed, or at least unexpected output</comment>
                            <comment id="14618166" author="prappo" created="Sat, 14 Oct 2023 03:37:58 -0700"  >In this particular case, the bug is provoked by a very similar construct:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* @deprecated - [#11329] - 3.15.0 - This type will be removed in the future. Do not reference it directly&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* &amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* &amp;lt;h3&amp;gt;Referencing &amp;lt;code&amp;gt;XYZ*Step&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt; types directly from client code&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
public interface RevokeFinalStep extends DDLQuery {&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
See &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jOOQ/jOOQ/blob/fb351a48f2c78e5b8e67fe55d454c49e7120dd75/jOOQ/src/main/java/org/jooq/RevokeFinalStep.java#L54&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jOOQ/jOOQ/blob/fb351a48f2c78e5b8e67fe55d454c49e7120dd75/jOOQ/src/main/java/org/jooq/RevokeFinalStep.java#L54&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8286470&quot; title=&quot;Support searching for sections in class/package javadoc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8286470&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8286470&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces headings (h1...h6) indexing and &amp;quot;&amp;lt;h3&amp;gt;Referencing&amp;quot; starts with the same letter (&amp;quot;R&amp;quot;) as &amp;quot;RevokeFinalStep&amp;quot;.</comment>
                            <comment id="14618025" author="prappo" created="Fri, 13 Oct 2023 04:17:18 -0700"  >[~leder] I&amp;#39;ll take it from here. Thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Yesterday, I composed a minimal example that leads to a similar behaviour ( CME being thrown from IndexWriter.addContents(IndexWriter.java:149) ). The example consists of @deprecated class being additionally indexed. The subtlety here is that the index term &amp;quot;S&amp;quot; starts with the same letter as the element is appears on:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;/**&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;* @deprecated {@index S}&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;*/&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public class SameFirstLetter {}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;ll check your repo to see if the bug you reported involves a similar construct.</comment>
